  <bioghist id="aspace_ba747fa940e226755d1502b52c0d2f04">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Dewitt Clinton Rodenhurst, January 26, 1855-May 5, 1946, was born in Westmoreland, NY and practiced medicine as a physician in Philadelphia, Jefferson County, NY.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_dae79816ec14dd16eb77e2261f001a2d">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Record of births and deaths of patients (1 v., 1880-1944); scrapbook of newspaper clippings, snapshots and photographs, letters, programs, and other otems (1 v., 1911-1945) of articles appearing in THE NORTH COUNTRY ADVANCE (1944-1945) and containing Dr. Rodenhurst's recollections of Philadelphia, New York, around 1880; printed items pertaining to the medical profession.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_5e0bb45ffc7f3049002284c51de2b3b8">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>DeWitt Clinton Rodenhurst papers, #1994. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
